<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The major eastern hub that families choose for its generous blocks, Capalaba State College, and the self-contained lifestyle that comes with living at the centre of the eastern residential corridor.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Capalaba sits approximately twenty-five kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD, occupying a central position in Brisbane's eastern residential corridor as the major service hub for the surrounding suburbs of Manly West, Belmont, Alexandra Hills, and Wynnum West. The suburb is defined by its large residential blocks, strong owner-occupier base, the well-regarded Capalaba State College, Capalaba Park shopping centre, and the practical self-contained lifestyle that comes from having extensive retail, health services, and community facilities close to home. Families who choose Capalaba have typically made a deliberate decision to move east, prioritising space, school options, and everyday convenience over the shorter commute that a closer-in address would offer.
    </p>
