    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Capalaba State College provides a Prep to Year 12 pathway in the local area, which is a meaningful draw for families who want their children to move through primary and secondary school without changing schools. For parents who are weighing school options while comparing suburbs in the eastern corridor, the presence of an established Prep to 12 college at the heart of the suburb simplifies a decision that is often one of the most complex variables in a family's suburb choice. When a buyer has resolved that question, they arrive at an open home with a different level of focus and motivation than someone still working through the options.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Capalaba is predominantly low-set family homes on generous blocks, with a mix of properties from the 1970s, 1980s and 1990s alongside a growing number of renovated and updated homes. The blocks in Capalaba are a genuine differentiator relative to the inner suburbs, giving families the outdoor space that is simply not available at comparable price points closer to the CBD. Sellers who understand how to present that space as the asset it is, and who price their campaign against the most recent comparable sales for their specific part of the suburb, are well-positioned to attract the motivated family buyers who are actively comparing the eastern corridor.
    </p>
